    "summary": "Paul is a true Project Management professional. He has in-depth Project Management knowledge and experience but also vast experience as Manager and as Trainer/ Coach of Professionals. Paul has excellent political, commercial and juridical skills. He is a good communicator and motivator. He is appointed \u2018Thought Leader Project Management\u2019 at Ordina for his extensive experience and strong vision in the field of project management. Paul is (international) speaker on congresses and seminars. As expert he is involved in publications on PMO and project management function profiles. He is IPMA Level B certified and an IPMA assessor for both the certification of professionals and for the Project Excellence Awards. Within IPMA he is the team leader for the improvement of the global certification system\n\nPaul\u2019s strength lays in his open communication, Paul creates cohesion between stakeholders in a project. Project Sponsors and the Project Team highly appreciate his clear vision and structured way of working. He is human oriented and knows how to extract the maximum from his team. He works from the motto \u2018promise is a promise\u2019 to meet expectations of the stakeholders.\n\nThrough his long experience in execution of project audits, project quality assurance and assessments of projects and project managers, Paul can pin point the required improvements to enhance the quality of project execution.\n\nPaul worked in various industry sectors: Petro Chemical Industry, Public sector, Defense, Telecommunications and cable networks. Apart from his project management experience, Paul worked as business unit manager for project management and consultancy for 4 years at KPN. He has also created and led eircom consult in Ireland as part of the joint venture between eircom and KPN/ Telia. \n\nCertified Project Manager IPMA level B\nIPMA/ Cito Assessor for IPMA certification\nCertified Program Manager MSP practitioner\n\nSpecialties: Project and program management\ncompetence development",
